    dc:creator "Ordines, Francesc; Ramírez-Amaro, Sergio; Calero, Belén; Farriols, Maria Teresa; Massutí, Enric" ;
    dc:date "2024" ;
    dc:title "A new species of the genus Ophiomyxa (Echinodermata: Ophiuroidea: Ophiomyxidae) from the Mallorca Channel seamounts in the western Mediterranean" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10720680>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10720682>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10720684>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10720686>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10720678>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10720688> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10720680>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Ophiomyxa xispa sp. nov. A: dorsal view of the holotype alive. B: dorsal view of the holotype preserved in ethanol. C: Disk integument showing the scales and ossicles. D: Detail of the jaw and genital slits. E: detail of proximal arm segments. F: dorsal arm plate. G: detail of an arm spine. Abbreviations: AdSh, adoral shield; AdShSp, adoral shield spine; AdGs, adradial genital scale; AbGs, abradial genital scale; CSP, comma-shaped plate; DAP, dorsal arm plate; GS, genital slit; IPa, infradental papilla; LAP, lateral arm plate; LOPa, lateral oral papilla; OP, oral plate; Os, ossicle; Osh, oral shield; Sc, scales; VAP-1, first ventral arm plate; VAP-2, second ventral arm plate; vT, ventralmost tooth." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10720680/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10720682>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Ophiomyxa xispa sp. nov. ossicles from the disk integument (A), and dorsal (B) and ventral (C) arm plates. Drawing by Núria Ordines." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10720682/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10720684>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Phylogenetic tree based on Bayesian inference for a COI fragment for Ophiomyxa species. Posterior probabilities are indicated near the nodes. The new species is indicated in bold face." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10720684/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10720686>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Limestone fragments collected from the rock dredge sampling station 18 during the INTEMARES-A22B_0718 survey. The holotype of Ophiomyxa xispa sp. nov. was collected from a crevice in the largest fragment." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10720686/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10720678>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Map of the Mallorca Channel seamounts showing the sampling stations carried out using rock dredge and beam trawl during the INTEMARES surveys from 2018 to 2020. In red the sampling station where the described specimen was collected." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10720678/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10720688>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Ophiomyxa pentagona, individual CBB-UIB 100487 after treatment in 4% sodium hypochlorite. A: ventral side of the arm showing a proximal ventral arm plate (VAP). B: two dorsal arm plates (DAP) removed from the arm. C: dorsal side of arm showing the DAPs covering the vertebrae. D: dorsal side of arm showing on one side the nude vertebra (V), the other side still covered by the DAP. LAP, lateral arm plate." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10720688/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

